channel.title: For all I create (Music, Art etc.)
channel.description:
I've been drawing all my life and writing music for roughly 5 years now and just started working in FL stuido on more game sounding music/tunes. So I thought anything i've worked on lately that's new I'd post here.
[b]Art: (2011 & Later)[/b] [url='https://img84.imageshack.us/img84/4572/notdeadmouse.png']Maus 2011[/url] [url='https://img828.imageshack.us/img828/5992/castlecrusher.png']Castle Crasher 2011[/url] [url='https://img62.imageshack.us/img62/7294/crabman.jpg']WIP Crab Man 2011[/url] [url='https://img851.imageshack.us/img851/9482/triffidcolour.jpg']Triffid Creation 2011[/url] [url='https://img37.imageshack.us/img37/199/templatec.png']HL Style Wall Texture (First Texture) 2011[/url] [url='https://img27.imageshack.us/img27/7016/dayofdead.png']Day Of The Dead (Fandango) 2011[/url] [url='https://a7.sphotos.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-snc6/226050_10150279291980970_539035969_7704946_6959040_n.jpg']Starcraft 2 Logo recreation 2011[/url] [url='https://img836.imageshack.us/img836/3756/finaldesign1.jpg']Gun Design 2010/2011[/url] [url='https://img406.imageshack.us/img406/2163/fivet.png']Female Warrior 2010[/url]
[b]Music (Instrumental Metal, Progressive):[/b] This is pretty much my solo band at the moment, have a listen if you're into it. I have some album songs up and some demos.
[url='https://www.facebook.com/pages/William-Bickle-Musician/134968406577692?sk=app_2405167945']William Bickle (Musician)[/url]
[b]Music (Game Music, Trance, Electronic):[/b] This i'm still new at, but I have made a few things so far. [url='https://uploads3.mp3songurls.com/1253083.mp3']Relax 2011[/url] [url='https://uploads3.mp3songurls.com/1253084.mp3']The Lab 2011[/url] [url='https://uploads3.mp3songurls.com/1253085.mp3']Chugga 2011[/url]
[b]Websites I've done:[/b] [url]https://tigonwelding.com.au/[/url]
So hope you enjoy. More to come!
Thanks!

item.description:
I do like the music, though. It’s a sort of old style video game sounding thingy. Although, it would sound better with a more ‘musical’ sound to it, rather than something I might hear from a chorus of floppy drives.
